truth: Iris...
iris: Oh, hi Truth.
truth: I wanted to ask you something.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]She stiffens a little. Like she already expects to say the wrong thing.[/i]
truth: Did you notice anything that might help? Even something small.
iris: Um... I-I was going to say something earlier, but...
iris: It's probably useless.
truth: Maybe not.
truth: Sometimes it's just about seeing it from a different angle.
iris: R-right...
truth: Go ahead.
iris: Um... when the lights went out...
iris: and that loud noise started...
iris: I kinda... freaked out.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]Her voice shrinks when she says it.[/i]
iris: I saw the door—like, where it should be—but...
iris: I didn’t want to go toward the noise.
iris: I just wanted to get away from it.
truth: So you moved back?
iris: Y-yeah...
iris: I think I was covering my ears too, I just...
iris: it was a lot, okay?
truth: I didn’t say anything.
iris: ...
iris: I kept stepping back, and then...
iris: I felt something poking my shoes.
truth: Something?
iris: L-like... sharp?
iris: It kept poking through when I moved.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]She looks down without meaning to. Like she can still feel it.[/i]
truth: And you didn’t check?
iris: N-no! I couldn’t see anything, and I didn’t want to—
iris: I just ran.
truth: Straight to the door?
iris: Y-yeah...
iris: I didn’t stop until I was outside.
truth: ...
truth: And that’s everything?
iris: ...
iris: Y-yeah.
iris: S-sorry... I told you it was useless.
truth: No.
truth: It helps.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]She relaxes. Just a little.[/i]
truth: Thanks, Iris.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]I don’t know if it actually helps.[/i]
truth: [color=#e85670][i]But she seems to need it to.[/i]
[signal arg="iris_account_complete"]